article.headline: SE Louisiana 56, Boise State 48
article.story: BOISE, Idaho (AP) -- Ricky Woods scored 23 points, pulled down seven rebounds and led a crucial second-half scoring surge as Southeastern Louisiana defeated Boise State 56-48 Sunday in the Boise State Invitational tournament. With Boise State (2-1) leading 38-32 with 12:10 left in the game, Woods led a 14-5 outburst with 10 points to put the Lions (3-0) ahead 46-43 with 6:25 remaining. Woods scored 16 of his game-high total in the second half. The teams were tied at 22 at the end of the first half, and Boise State pulled out to the 38-32 lead on the shooting of Kareem Lloyd and Jermaine Blackburn. Each scored 12 points to lead the Broncos. Southeastern Louisiana hit only one 3-point field goal, but shot 11 more field goal attempts. Boise State was plagued by poor shooting, hitting only 18 of 46, and also committed 24 turnovers.
